   <text>
      <body>
         <div type="letter">
            <pb n="1" facs="Edgeworth_Harvard_604762_1848-12-20_page01.jpg"/>
            <opener>
               <dateline>
                  <note>51</note>
                  <placeName ref="./Placeography.xml#Edgeworthstown_IE">Edgeworths Town</placeName>
                  <date when="1848-12-20">Dec<hi rend="superscript">r</hi> 20<hi rend="superscript">th</hi> 1848</date>
               </dateline>
               <salute>
                           My dear <persName ref="./Personography.xml#AshbX1">D<hi rend="superscript">r.</hi> Ashburner</persName>
               </salute>
            </opener>
            <p/>
            <p>Your friend <persName ref="./Personography.xml#WilsL1">Lestock<lb/>
                    Wilson</persName> (to whom I have<lb/>
                    just been reading a<lb/>
                    letter I <choice>
                  <orig>recd</orig>
                  <reg>received</reg>
               </choice> this morning<lb/>
               from <persName ref="./Personography.xml#TickA1">M<hi rend="superscript">rs</hi>. <choice>
                     <orig>Tickenor</orig>
                     <reg>Ticknor</reg>
                  </choice>
               </persName>
               <hi rend="underline">wife</hi>
               <lb/>
               or <hi rend="underline">lady</hi> of <persName ref="./Personography.xml#TickG1">Prof<hi rend="superscript">r</hi>
                  <choice>
                     <orig>Tickenor</orig>
                     <reg>Ticknor</reg>
                  </choice>
               </persName>
               <lb/>
               of <placeName ref="./Placeography.xml#Boston_MA_US">Boston</placeName>) thinks that<lb/>
                    you may be interested<lb/>
                    in the account of a <add>new</add> discovery<lb/>
                    - at least of a discovery new<lb/>
               to us - <persName ref="./Personography.xml#EdgeF3">M<hi rend="superscript">rs</hi>.Wilson</persName>has copied the<lb/>
                    paragraph in this letter for you -<lb/>
            </p>
            <closer>
                    With best wishes &amp; sincere regards I<lb/>
                    am dear <persName ref="./Personography.xml#AshbX1">D<hi rend="superscript">r.</hi> Ashburner</persName> truly yours<lb/>
               <persName ref="./Personography.xml#EdgeM1">Maria Edgeworth</persName>
               <lb/>
            </closer>
         </div>
      </body>
      <back/>
